    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-08T10:28:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-08T10:28:00-05:00" n="456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/5–854: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d456fn1">Drafted by the Secretary of State.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-08T11:28:00-04:00"
                            >May 8, 1954—11:28 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 42. For <persName corresp="#p_SWB1"
                        >Smith</persName> from Secretary. Assume you have text my last night
                        address.<note n="2" xml:id="d456fn2">Dated May 7, <ref target="#pg_720">p.
                            720</ref>.</note> The reference to “proper conditions” under which US
                    went into Korea was designed to suggest by analogy the conditions which US would
                    want to settle before becoming belligerent in Indochina. We assume that French
                    will have gotten the point and realize that we are ready to talk with them about
                    internationalizing the war <pb facs="0755" n="729" xml:id="pg_729"/> if they
                    come to conclusion that this is preferable to the harsh terms which no doubt
                    Communists will seek to extract. Also, <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>, it
                    might not be indispensable that the <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>
                    participates at the outset.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
